<div id="review_79506261" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/79506261" />
    <a title="Claire S" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1888594-claire-s"><img alt="Claire S" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1235005193p2/1888594.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/79506261?book_show_action=true">Dec 01, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Claire S" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Claire S" href="/user/show/1888594-claire-s">Claire S</a>
      </span>

          is currently reading it


          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780451159526" href="/book/show/853163.To_Be_Young_Gifted_and_Black">review of another edition</a>


          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Claire by: </span>
      Universe
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1888594-claire-s?shelf=a-2-interest-wo-urgency">a-2-interest-wo-urgency</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1888594-claire-s?shelf=id-constructs-race-gender">id-constructs-race-gender</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1888594-claire-s?shelf=fiction-not-at-all">fiction-not-at-all</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1888594-claire-s?shelf=women">women</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1888594-claire-s?shelf=historical">historical</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1888594-claire-s?shelf=pol-historical">pol-historical</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1888594-claire-s?shelf=f_interpretations">f_interpretations</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1888594-claire-s?shelf=form_complexia">form_complexia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1888594-claire-s?shelf=struggles-of-use">struggles-of-use</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1888594-claire-s?shelf=obama-term-1">obama-term-1</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer79506261" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15894961516466946137">Had heard of this, and formed and impression of this, based on other things I read in Women&apos;s Studies in the 80&apos;s. But for the first time picked up a copy at my daughter&apos;s school library, waiting for a meeting to start. I really like the tone of it.. Another Chicagoan! Looking forward to reading it all.<br/><br/>Her description of the way the ghetto-izing schools of Chicago intentionally robbed their students of an education, and the effect on her, is shocking. Also her description of her Dad&apos;s efforts to</span>
  <span id="freeText15894961516466946137" style="display:none">Had heard of this, and formed and impression of this, based on other things I read in Women's Studies in the 80's. But for the first time picked up a copy at my daughter's school library, waiting for a meeting to start. I really like the tone of it.. Another Chicagoan! Looking forward to reading it all.<br /><br />Her description of the way the ghetto-izing schools of Chicago intentionally robbed their students of an education, and the effect on her, is shocking. Also her description of her Dad's efforts to gain justice the 'right' way, and, again, the effects on her, hard to even imagine. <br /><br />The format - part prose, part play - is jangling, but worth it of course. <br /><br />It's sooo tragic how young she died (at age 34 in 1965)! All sixty-one of the artists who took place in the telling of 'Lorraine Hansberry in Her Own Words' to commemorate her on the second anniversary of her death, including Anne Bancroft, Lauren Bacall, Ralph Bellamy, Bette Davis, Ruby Dee, Colleen Dewhurst, Rita Moreno, Paul Robeson, Sidney Poitier, Maureen Stapleton, Rod Steiger and so many more - I'm even bigger fans of all of them.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15894961516466946137" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


