<span id="freeTextContainer9281714206318059020">Lorraine Hansberry was a brilliant playwright, author, and critic. It is very sad that she died so young. However, This brilliant account of her life, told in her own words, is a treasure. Many people do not even realize that her father&apos;s famous U.S. Supreme Court caseabolished the practice of restrictive covenants and the case still in which her retains the Hansberry name. Restrictive Covenants allowed for racial segregation in the purchase of real property, specifically residential property, a</span>
  <span id="freeText9281714206318059020" style="display:none">Lorraine Hansberry was a brilliant playwright, author, and critic. It is very sad that she died so young. However, This brilliant account of her life, told in her own words, is a treasure. Many people do not even realize that her father's famous U.S. Supreme Court caseabolished the practice of restrictive covenants and the case still in which her retains the Hansberry name. Restrictive Covenants allowed for racial segregation in the purchase of real property, specifically residential property, and this became a theme of Ms. Hansberry's major play "Raisin in the Sun." I love this book </span>
  <a data-text-id="9281714206318059020" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

