<div id="review_924457578" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/924457578" />
    <a title="Cynthia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29877763-cynthia"><img alt="Cynthia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1404418390p2/29877763.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/924457578?book_show_action=true">Apr 30, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cynthia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cynthia" href="/user/show/29877763-cynthia">Cynthia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780451159526" href="/book/show/853163.To_Be_Young_Gifted_and_Black">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29877763-cynthia?shelf=african-american-authors">african-american-authors</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29877763-cynthia?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29877763-cynthia?shelf=autobiography">autobiography</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer924457578" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6108615869541142427">Hansberry&apos;s &quot;To Be Young, Gifted and Black &quot; is the story of a young Chi-town African-American woman who took the New York theater scene by storm with her play, A Raisin in the Sun. Hansberry&apos;s truths about the black experience in levels of anger, love, bitterness, laughter, and defiantly pride in a voice that is all Hansberry in her element.<br/><br/>Picked up To Be Young, Gifted and Black in junior high school ( my junior high school was named Lorraine Hansberry I. S. 167) which started my curiosity as </span>
  <span id="freeText6108615869541142427" style="display:none">Hansberry's "To Be Young, Gifted and Black " is the story of a young Chi-town African-American woman who took the New York theater scene by storm with her play, A Raisin in the Sun. Hansberry's truths about the black experience in levels of anger, love, bitterness, laughter, and defiantly pride in a voice that is all Hansberry in her element.<br /><br />Picked up To Be Young, Gifted and Black in junior high school ( my junior high school was named Lorraine Hansberry I. S. 167) which started my curiosity as to who was this Hansberry person and why was her name chosen for my then school. Read "To Be Young... " and was an instant fan, after came of course "A Raisin in the Sun". You don't read Hansberry, you experience her.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6108615869541142427" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


