<div id="review_981242932" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/981242932" />
    <a title="Charissa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23328341-charissa"><img alt="Charissa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1514043390p2/23328341.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/981242932?book_show_action=true">Jun 29, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Charissa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Charissa" href="/user/show/23328341-charissa">Charissa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780451159526" href="/book/show/853163.To_Be_Young_Gifted_and_Black">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer981242932" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1083262251298703416">Intertwining plays with essays with letters with her thoughts, this book gave an amazing in depth look into Lorraine hansberry and the contributions she has made to society. Her notion that it&apos;s not a negro condition but a human condition lends itself to her writing as that all humans are equal, I a powerful chord that still strikes today as there are still injustices and inequalities in our society.</span>
  <span id="freeText1083262251298703416" style="display:none">Intertwining plays with essays with letters with her thoughts, this book gave an amazing in depth look into Lorraine hansberry and the contributions she has made to society. Her notion that it's not a negro condition but a human condition lends itself to her writing as that all humans are equal, I a powerful chord that still strikes today as there are still injustices and inequalities in our society.</span>
